  "title": "Creating a custom range facet with `connectRange` AND using routing fires an incorrect warning",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\nUsing any form of routing with a custom range facet created using `connectRange` will fire a warning about `range` needing either `rangeInput` or `rangeSlider`.\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce the behavior:**\r\n\r\n1. Go to https://g2vyw.csb.app/?instant_search%5Brange%5D%5Bprice%5D=22%3A321321\r\n1. Open your console\r\n1. See incorrect warning\r\n\r\n**Live reproduction:**\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/objective-darwin-g2vyw?file=/src/app.js\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNo warning should be fired\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n- OS: macOS\r\n- Browser: Chrome \r\n- Version: 83\r\n- `InstantSearch.js` Version 4.7.0 \r\n",
